    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB - TILT: 9600 AND 9700 SLEEPER AND NON-SLEEPER CABS -
        SHEET METAL REPAIRS - REMOVE PANEL RIVETS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
        <title>REMOVE PANEL RIVETS</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Center punch all rivets (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1600661">Figure 61</hotlnk>) in panel to be removed and also center punch the spot
                welds to be removed along windshield fence (edge).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1600661" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1600661" filename="../figg16/g1600661.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 61. Center Punching Rivets and Spot Welds</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. WINDSHIELD FENCE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SPOT WELDS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. CENTER PUNCH</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Drill a small pilot hole in each rivet head and in each spot weld (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1600662">Figure 62</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1600662" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1600662" filename="../figg16/g1600662.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 62. Drilling Pilot Holes</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Drill 3/16 inch (4.76mm) diameter hole in each rivet head.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Use drill of same size or slightly smaller than shank of rivet to be removed. Do not drill
                        deeper than head of rivet. If you do, you may need a larger rivet to fill the hole for
                        subsequent fastening.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Cut off rivet head with hammer and chisel (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1600663">Figure 63</hotlnk>). Do not elongate rivet hole.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1600663" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1600663" filename="../figg16/g1600663.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 63. Removing Rivet Heads</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tap out rivet shank or stem.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
